  "text": "Correlation coefficients between the QuickDASH-JSSH-DS and the SF-36 were obtained. Correlation coefficients between the QuickDASH-JSSH and VAS for pain were obtained, and the criterion-based validity investigation looked at the following hypothesis: the correlation between the QuickDASH-JSSH and VAS for pain would be high. The responsiveness was examined by calculating the standardized response mean (SRM; mean change/SD) [CITATION_1] and effect size (mean change/SD of baseline value) [CITATION_2] after carpal tunnel release of the patients with carpal tunnel syndrome.",
